<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-721-748  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 721 748.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 7 1990 v4 n27 p31(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Heizer converts stacks to Windows Toolbook. (Heizer SoftwareInc.'s ConvertIt! data conversion software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cohen, Raines.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Heizer Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   ConvertIt! (Data conversion software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionData ConversionSoftware PackagesStackware.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Raines CohenandM;Pleasant Hill, Calif.andP;  -- Heizer Software last week shipped ConvertIt!, anapplication that converts HyperCard 1.x stacks into &quot;books&quot; usable byAsymetrix Corp.'s ToolBook under Windows 3.0.andM;ConvertIt! translates stacks into an intermediate file format called HIFF(Hyper-media Interchange File Format) for transfer to DOS machines andeventual translation into ToolBook books.andM;ToolBook developers can use ConvertIt! to translate complete stacks; toreconstruct all or some of the objects in a stack; to translate HyperTalkcode into OpenScript, ToolBook's native language; and to port bit maps andicons from a stack into ToolBook as paint objects.andP;  External commands (XCMDs)and functions are machine-dependent and cannot be translated directly.andM;ConvertIt!, which sells for $199, typically converts 80 percent or more ofstacks, the company said.andP;  An upgrade due later this year will supportHyperCard 2.0.andM;Asymetrix last week announced a $450 ToolBook Author's Resource Kit,including several utilities and royalty-free distribution rights to theruntime version of ToolBook.andM;Heizer Software can be reached at P.O. Box 232019, Pleasant Hill, Calif.andO;94523; (415) 943-7667; (800) 888-7667.andO;</TEXT></DOC>